---
// Scroll-driven demonstration framed as the Institut finally processing
// Mark Twain's 1880 complaint about German ("The Awful German Language").
// His case file is exhibited, the article table collapses, the English
// precedent is cited, then a Kafka sentence is corrected rule by rule and
// stamped. Progress is driven by an IntersectionObserver setting
// data-step / data-stage on the section; visuals react via CSS.
---

<section class="scrolly" id="demo" data-step="0" data-stage="file">
  <header class="scrolly-lead">
    <p class="kicker">Amtliche Vorführung</p>
    <h2>German, simplified.</h2>
    <p class="sub">The simplification procedure, demonstrated. Scroll to proceed.</p>
  </header>

  <div class="scrolly-body">
    <div class="scrolly-stage">
      <!-- Stage A: the Twain case file -->
      <div class="stage-card stage-file">
        <div class="card-head">
          <span>Az. 1880-TW-001</span>
          <span>Antrag auf Sprachreform</span>
        </div>
        <p class="file-meta">
          Antragsteller: Twain, M. (Heidelberg)<br />
          Eingegangen: 1880 &nbsp;·&nbsp; Status: <strong>offen</strong>
        </p>
        <blockquote class="file-quote">
          Every noun has a gender, and there is no sense or system in the
          distribution; so the gender of each must be learned separately and
          by heart. There is no other way. &hellip; In German, a young lady
          has no sex, while a turnip has.
        </blockquote>
        <p class="file-attrib">— M. Twain, <em>A Tramp Abroad</em> (1880)</p>
        <div class="file-annex" data-at="1">
          <p class="annex-label">Anlage: Beweisstück</p>
          <div class="annex-dialogue">
            <p><span class="speaker">Gretchen.</span> Wilhelm, where is the turnip?</p>
            <p><span class="speaker">Wilhelm.</span> She has gone to the kitchen.</p>
            <p><span class="speaker">Gretchen.</span> Where is the accomplished and beautiful English maiden?</p>
            <p><span class="speaker">Wilhelm.</span> It has gone to the opera.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Stage B: the declension table -->
      <div class="stage-card stage-table">
        <div class="card-head">
          <span>Anlage 1</span>
          <span>Bestimmter Artikel, Standarddeutsch</span>
        </div>
        <table>
          <thead>
            <tr>
              <th></th><th>Mask.</th><th>Fem.</th><th>Neut.</th><th>Plural</th>
            </tr>
          </thead>
          <tbody>
            <tr>
              <th>Nominativ</th>
              <td><del>der</del><ins>die</ins></td>
              <td class="stays">die</td>
              <td><del>das</del><ins>die</ins></td>
              <td class="stays">die</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <th>Akkusativ</th>
              <td><del>den</del><ins>die</ins></td>
              <td class="stays">die</td>
              <td><del>das</del><ins>die</ins></td>
              <td class="stays">die</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <th>Dativ</th>
              <td><del>dem</del><ins>die</ins></td>
              <td><del>der</del><ins>die</ins></td>
              <td><del>dem</del><ins>die</ins></td>
              <td><del>den</del><ins>die</ins></td>
            </tr>
            <tr class="gen">
              <th>Genitiv</th>
              <td><del>des</del><ins>der</ins></td>
              <td class="stays">der</td>
              <td><del>des</del><ins>der</ins></td>
              <td class="stays">der</td>
            </tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
        <p class="table-verdict">Sechzehn Felder. Zwei Formen.</p>
      </div>

      <!-- Stage C: the English precedent -->
      <div class="stage-card stage-precedent">
        <div class="card-head">
          <span>Präzedenzfall</span>
          <span>Englisch, erledigt ca. 1300</span>
        </div>
        <table class="prec-table">
          <thead>
            <tr>
              <th>Altenglisch</th>
              <th></th>
              <th>Englisch, heute</th>
            </tr>
          </thead>
          <tbody>
            <tr>
              <td>se mōna <span class="gloss">(m.)</span></td>
              <td class="arrow">→</td>
              <td><ins>the</ins> moon</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td>sēo sunne <span class="gloss">(f.)</span></td>
              <td class="arrow">→</td>
              <td><ins>the</ins> sun</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td>þæt wīf <span class="gloss">(n.)</span></td>
              <td class="arrow">→</td>
              <td><ins>the</ins> wife</td>
            </tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
        <p class="table-verdict prec-verdict">
          Erledigt. Keine Beschwerden seit 700 Jahren.
        </p>
      </div>

      <!-- Stage D: the sentence under processing -->
      <div class="stage-card stage-doc">
        <div class="card-head">
          <span>Formblatt AL-2</span>
          <span>Antrag auf Vereinfachung</span>
        </div>
        <p class="doc-source">
          Eingang: F. Kafka, <em>Die Verwandlung</em> (1915), Satz 1
        </p>
        <p class="doc-sentence">
          Als Gregor Samsa
          <span class="tok" data-at="6"><del>eines Morgens</del><ins>ein Morgen</ins></span>
          aus
          <span class="tok" data-at="8"><del>unruhigen</del><ins>unruhige</ins></span>
          <span class="tok" data-at="7"><del>Träumen</del><ins>Träume</ins></span>
          erwachte, fand er sich in
          <span class="tok" data-at="9"><del>seinem</del><ins>sein</ins></span>
          Bett zu
          <span class="tok" data-at="6"><del>einem</del><ins>ein</ins></span>
          <span class="tok" data-at="8"><del>ungeheueren</del><ins>ungeheure</ins></span>
          Ungeziefer verwandelt.
        </p>
        <div class="doc-chips" aria-hidden="true">
          <span class="chip" data-at="6">§2a</span>
          <span class="chip" data-at="7">§3a</span>
          <span class="chip" data-at="8">§4a</span>
          <span class="chip" data-at="9">§7c</span>
        </div>
        <div class="doc-clean" data-at="10">
          <p class="clean-label">Reinschrift</p>
          <p class="clean-sentence">
            Als Gregor Samsa ein Morgen aus unruhige Träume erwachte, fand er
            sich in sein Bett zu ein ungeheure Ungeziefer verwandelt.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="stamp" data-at="10" aria-hidden="true">
          <span class="stamp-emblem"></span>
          <span class="stamp-line1">Amtlich vereinfacht</span>
          <span class="stamp-line2">Geprüft · §1–§10</span>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="scrolly-steps">
      <div class="step" data-step="0">
        <p class="step-kicker">Vorgang 1880-TW-001</p>
        <p>
          In 1880, an American author filed a detailed complaint about the
          German language, together with a proposal for its reform. The
          file has remained open since.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="step" data-step="1">
        <p class="step-kicker">Beweisaufnahme</p>
        <p>
          Supporting evidence was attached. The Institut has since verified
          the examples: a turnip is <em>she</em>, a young lady is
          <em>it</em>, a tree is male, its buds are female, its leaves are
          neuter. No error on the applicant's part could be established.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="step" data-step="2">
        <p class="step-kicker">Befund</p>
        <p>
          The complaint has merit. Standard German declines its definite
          article across three genders, four cases and two numbers: sixteen
          slots, six forms, and no system by which to learn them.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="step" data-step="3">
        <p class="step-kicker">Abhilfe · §1a, §1b</p>
        <p>
          Alman abolishes fifteen of them. Every non-genitive context
          receives <strong>die</strong>; the genitive receives
          <strong>der</strong>. The applicant's first proposal — to leave
          out the dative case — is hereby exceeded.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="step" data-step="4">
        <p class="step-kicker">Präzedenzfall</p>
        <p>
          The remedy follows precedent. English — also a Germanic language —
          once declined the same three genders: <em>se mōna</em>, the
          he-moon; <em>sēo sunne</em>, the she-sun; <em>þæt wīf</em>, the
          it-wife. By the fourteenth century every one of them had become
          <strong>the</strong>. Nobody has missed them since.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="step" data-step="5">
        <p class="step-kicker">Eingang</p>
        <p>
          The procedure extends to whole sentences. For demonstration, one
          is submitted for processing: the opening of Kafka's
          <em>Die Verwandlung</em>.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="step" data-step="6">
        <p class="step-kicker">§2a</p>
        <p>
          The indefinite article adopts its invariant base form
          <strong>ein</strong>. Case endings are discarded:
          <em>eines Morgens</em> and <em>einem</em> are corrected.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="step" data-step="7">
        <p class="step-kicker">§3a</p>
        <p>
          Case endings on nouns are eliminated. The dative plural
          <em>Träumen</em> loses its <em>-n</em> and reverts to the plain
          plural <em>Träume</em>.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="step" data-step="8">
        <p class="step-kicker">§4a</p>
        <p>
          The applicant reported he would "rather decline two drinks than
          one German adjective." The matter is resolved: all adjective
          endings regularize to an invariant <strong>-e</strong>.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="step" data-step="9">
        <p class="step-kicker">§7c</p>
        <p>
          Possessive determiners keep their bare base form in all
          non-genitive contexts: <em>seinem Bett</em> is corrected to
          <em>sein Bett</em>.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="step" data-step="10">
        <p class="step-kicker">Bescheid</p>
        <p>
          Processing complete. What English accomplished seven hundred years
          ago, Alman applies to German: a gender-equitable world language.
          File 1880-TW-001 is closed. The full procedure is codified below
          in <a href="#definite-articles">§1–§10</a>.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<script>
  const section = document.getElementById("demo")!;
  const steps = section.querySelectorAll<HTMLElement>(".step");

  function apply(step: number) {
    section.dataset.step = String(step);
    section.dataset.stage =
      step >= 5 ? "doc" : step === 4 ? "precedent" : step >= 2 ? "table" : "file";
    section.classList.toggle("collapsed", step >= 3);
    section
      .querySelectorAll<HTMLElement>("[data-at]")
      .forEach((el) => {
        el.classList.toggle("done", step >= Number(el.dataset.at));
      });
  }

  const observer = new IntersectionObserver(
    (entries) => {
      for (const entry of entries) {
        if (entry.isIntersecting) {
          apply(Number((entry.target as HTMLElement).dataset.step));
        }
      }
    },
    { rootMargin: "-40% 0px -50% 0px" },
  );
  steps.forEach((el) => observer.observe(el));
</script>

<style>
  /* Full-bleed breakout from the 50rem main column */
  .scrolly {
    width: 100vw;
    margin-left: calc(50% - 50vw);
    padding: 1rem 1.25rem 4rem;
  }

  .scrolly-lead {
    max-width: var(--content-width);
    margin: 0 auto 1rem;
    text-align: center;
    padding: 1.5rem 0 0;
  }

  .kicker,
  .step-kicker {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 0.72rem;
    letter-spacing: 0.14em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--grey-1);
  }

  .scrolly-lead h2 {
    border: none;
    padding: 0;
    margin: 0.4rem 0 0.3rem;
    font-size: 2.3rem;
  }

  .scrolly-lead .sub {
    margin: 0;
    color: var(--grey-1);
  }

  .scrolly-body {
    max-width: 66rem;
    margin: 0 auto;
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: minmax(15rem, 20rem) 1fr;
    gap: 3rem;
  }

  /* ---------- Stage ---------- */

  .scrolly-stage {
    order: 2;
    position: sticky;
    top: 0;
    height: 100vh;
    height: 100dvh;
    display: grid;
    align-items: center;
    justify-items: center;
  }

  .stage-card {
    background: #ffffff;
    border: 1px solid var(--ink);
    border-radius: 2px;
    padding: 1.5rem 1.75rem 1.75rem;
    width: 100%;
    max-width: 34rem;
    grid-area: 1 / 1;
    position: relative;
    opacity: 0;
    visibility: hidden;
    transition: opacity 0.45s ease, visibility 0.45s;
  }

  [data-stage="file"] .stage-file,
  [data-stage="table"] .stage-table,
  [data-stage="precedent"] .stage-precedent,
  [data-stage="doc"] .stage-doc {
    opacity: 1;
    visibility: visible;
  }

  .card-head {
    display: flex;
    justify-content: space-between;
    gap: 1rem;
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 0.68rem;
    letter-spacing: 0.1em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--grey-1);
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--ink);
    padding-bottom: 0.55rem;
    margin-bottom: 1.1rem;
  }

  /* Case-file stage */
  .file-meta {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 0.75rem;
    line-height: 1.8;
    color: var(--grey-1);
    margin: 0 0 1.1rem;
  }

  .file-meta strong {
    color: var(--fail-red);
    font-weight: 400;
  }

  .file-quote {
    margin: 0;
    padding: 0;
    border: none;
    color: var(--ink);
    font-style: italic;
    font-size: 1.02rem;
    line-height: 1.75;
  }

  .file-attrib {
    margin: 0.7rem 0 0;
    font-size: 0.85rem;
    color: var(--grey-1);
  }

  .file-annex {
    border-top: 1px solid var(--grey-2);
    margin-top: 1.1rem;
    padding-top: 0.9rem;
    opacity: 0;
    transition: opacity 0.5s ease 0.15s;
  }

  .file-annex.done {
    opacity: 1;
  }

  .annex-label {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 0.68rem;
    letter-spacing: 0.12em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--grey-1);
    margin: 0 0 0.6rem;
  }

  .annex-dialogue p {
    margin: 0 0 0.35rem;
    font-size: 0.95rem;
    font-style: italic;
  }

  .annex-dialogue .speaker {
    font-style: normal;
    font-weight: 600;
  }

  /* Table stage */
  .stage-table table {
    margin: 0.5rem 0 0;
  }

  .stage-table th {
    border: none;
    font-size: 0.72rem;
    padding: 0.4rem 0.6rem;
  }

  .stage-table tbody th {
    text-align: left;
    color: var(--grey-1);
    font-weight: 500;
  }

  .stage-table td {
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--grey-2);
    padding: 0.5rem 0.6rem;
    font-family: var(--font-din);
    font-weight: 600;
    font-size: 1.35rem;
    width: 21%;
  }

  .stage-table td del {
    text-decoration: none;
    transition: opacity 0.5s ease;
  }

  .stage-table td ins {
    display: none;
    text-decoration: none;
    color: var(--form-blue);
  }

  .stage-table td.stays {
    transition: color 0.5s ease;
  }

  .collapsed .stage-table td del {
    display: none;
  }

  .collapsed .stage-table td ins {
    display: inline;
  }

  .collapsed .stage-table td.stays {
    color: var(--form-blue);
  }

  .table-verdict {
    margin: 1.2rem 0 0;
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 0.78rem;
    letter-spacing: 0.08em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--grey-1);
    opacity: 0;
    transition: opacity 0.5s ease 0.3s;
  }

  .collapsed .table-verdict {
    opacity: 1;
  }

  /* Precedent stage */
  .prec-table {
    width: 100%;
    border-collapse: collapse;
    margin: 0.5rem 0 0;
  }

  .prec-table th {
    font-family: var(--font-din);
    font-weight: 600;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.04em;
    font-size: 0.72rem;
    text-align: left;
    border: none;
    padding: 0.4rem 0.6rem;
  }

  .prec-table td {
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--grey-2);
    padding: 0.55rem 0.6rem;
    font-family: var(--font-din);
    font-weight: 600;
    font-size: 1.25rem;
  }

  .prec-table td ins {
    text-decoration: none;
    color: var(--form-blue);
  }

  .prec-table .arrow {
    color: var(--grey-1);
    font-weight: 400;
    width: 2rem;
    text-align: center;
